==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Duodenum
<hw>Du`o*de"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
<ets>duodeni</ets> twelve each: cf. F. <ets>duodenum</ets>. So called
because its length is about twelve fingers' breadth.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The part of the small intestines between the
stomach and the jejunum. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <xex>Digestive
apparatus</xex>, under <er>Digestive</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duograph</ent>⟦br⟧
